# Changelog

## 1.0.4 — 2026-03-11

- New `template` skill — guided interview that produces reusable reference docs for recurring types of work; includes discovery phase, readiness check, and coverage confirmation before drafting
- `feedback` skill sharpened: added explicit Filter step before delivery ("would I act on this?"), trimmed Deliver step to remove redundancy


## 1.0.3 — 2026-03-11

- `blueprint` skill renamed to `draft` — reframed as iterative proposed-changes doc rather than auditable step list; output format is now `### Proposed Changes` with inline em-dash rationale
- Guard secrets moved from Guidance to Hard Boundaries — makes the no-override contract explicit
- Workflow section rewritten as four named principles: Read the doc, One suggestion, Earn the introduction, Design problems go back to workshop
- Workshop doc format updated: `Key Decisions` replaced with per-idea status blocks carrying confidence, date, and four readiness heuristics (complete, reasoning, scoped, templated)


## 1.0.2 — 2026-03-11

- `explain` skill is now always inline — no file output. Explanations live in the conversation.


## 1.0.1 — 2026-03-11

- Formalized skill forking via `context: fork` frontmatter, replacing ad-hoc subagent convention
- Status file is now a running log — completed items move to "Done" instead of being deleted
- Added session-start sync: scans `.tab/` subdirectories and adds untracked files to status
- Cleaned up README skill sections — removed trigger lines, kept slash commands
- Aligned draw-dino description to reactive trigger convention

## 1.0.0 — 2026-03-11

Initial release.

- Tab persona — voice, rules, behaviors, session-to-session status tracking
- Five skills: workshop, blueprint, feedback, explain, draw-dino
- Plugin manifest and settings for automatic persona activation
- Created lightweight `.tab/status.md` workbench model
- CLAUDE.md scoped to contributor guidance
